Activity: A2 – Discover security concepts used in public space

Objective
The goal of this activity is to observe and analyse security concepts used in public spaces.

Method
I walked around shops in Perth CBD and identified security measures such as CCTV cameras, access card doors, and alarm systems.

Findings
I discovered the following security implementations:
1. CCTV cameras - used to monitor customers and staff activity, and to prevent theft or vandalism
2. Security guards - used as a human security layer
4. Alarm systems - to make sure no one walks out of the store without paying for a product
5. Physical security tags - often attached to expensive products such as electronics which can't be removed until purchased

Security Principle
These systems support confidentiality, integrity, and availability.

Evidence


Reflection
This activity helped me understand how security concepts are applied in real environments.
